title: Grateful Dead Live at Nassau Coliseum on 1980-05-16
lineage: 2 x Nakamichi CM700 w/ EQ 26th Row Center> Sony TC-D5 (dolby encode) Transfer: MAC > Nakamichi DR-1 > Grace Design Lunatec V3 [Pre-Only] > Korg MR-1000 > DSF [1-bit 5.6448 MHz Stereo] > Korg AudioGate > WAV [24/96] > ? > flac16; Taped by: Barry Glassberg
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Promised Land, High Time, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Row Jimmy, Minglewood Blues, Ramble On Rose, Looks Like Rain, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider

Set 2

Feel Like A Stranger-> Althea-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Morning Dew-> Around & Around-> Johnny B. Goode, E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text:
Love it Not sure if you ever read the reviews Barry but your recordings are top of the line. During my time frame of touring to boot. 
 This one is just smoking.  All the Jerry sweet songs  High time, Row jimmy, The Dew and my all time fav encore Brokedown Palace

Great recording, so-so performance. The bass is stronger than most aud. tapes, so lottsa Phil!  But the performance is just OK. Most of Jerry's tunes are just TOO SLOWWWW. The Dew is rare, but also really sleepy and a bit sloppy.  5 days before this show, 5/11/80, is a total Jerry fiesta, he's TOTALLY ON.  A month later, in Alaska, is a perfect 3 nite run.
